OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fconstant abuse' to boy who 
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Flost finger                
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, An 11-year old boy who lost his finger 
OL,6, reportedly fleeing bullies was         
OL,7, subjected to months of racist abuse and
OL,8, bullying, his mother has said.         
OL,10,FRaheem Bailey, a pupil at Abertillery  
OL,11,FLearning Community in Blaenau Gwent,   
OL,12,Fcaught his finger climbing a fence     
OL,13,Ftrying to escape.                      
OL,15,F"It seems like he has constantly been  
OL,16,Fbullied," his mother Shantal said.     
OL,18,FBlaenau Gwent council said at the time 
OL,19,Fof the incident the safety and         
OL,20,Fwell-being of learners was paramount.  
